def _get_items(self) -> List[v.ListItem]:
        """
        Create the list of items inside the folder.

        Returns:
            list of items inside the selected folder
        """
        folder = self.folder

        list_dir = [el for el in folder.glob("*/") if not el.name.startswith(".")]

        if self.extentions:
            list_dir = [
                el for el in list_dir if el.is_dir() or el.suffix in self.extentions
            ]

        folder_list = []
        file_list = []

        for el in list_dir:

            if el.is_dir():
                icon = self.ICON_STYLE[""]["icon"]
                color = self.ICON_STYLE[""]["color"][v.theme.dark]
            elif el.suffix in self.ICON_STYLE.keys():
                icon = self.ICON_STYLE[el.suffix]["icon"]
                color = self.ICON_STYLE[el.suffix]["color"][v.theme.dark]
            else:
                icon = self.ICON_STYLE["DEFAULT"]["icon"]
                color = self.ICON_STYLE["DEFAULT"]["color"][v.theme.dark]

            children = [
                v.ListItemAction(children=[v.Icon(color=color, children=[icon])]),
                v.ListItemContent(
                    children=[v.ListItemTitle(children=[el.stem + el.suffix])]
                ),
            ]

            if el.is_dir():
                folder_list.append(v.ListItem(value=str(el), children=children))
            else:
                file_size = su.get_file_size(el)
                children.append(
                    v.ListItemActionText(class_="ml-1", children=[file_size])
                )
                file_list.append(v.ListItem(value=str(el), children=children))

        folder_list = humansorted(folder_list, key=lambda x: x.value)
        file_list = humansorted(file_list, key=lambda x: x.value)

        # Calculate current depth from starting folder
        current_depth = 0
        try:
            relative = folder.relative_to(self.folder)
            current_depth = len(relative.parts)
        except ValueError:
            # folder is not relative to starting folder
            pass

        # Filter out parent items that would exceed max_depth
        parent_item = v.ListItem(
            value=str(folder.parent),
            children=[
                v.ListItemAction(
                    children=[
                        v.Icon(
                            color=self.ICON_STYLE["PARENT"]["color"][v.theme.dark],
                            children=[self.ICON_STYLE["PARENT"]["icon"]],
                        )
                    ]
                ),
                v.ListItemContent(
                    children=[v.ListItemTitle(children=[f".. /{folder.parent.stem}"])]
                ),
            ],
        )

        # Only add parent item if we can navigate up without exceeding max_depth
        # max_depth=0 means only parent navigation (no going down)
        # max_depth>0 means we can navigate up and down
        if current_depth < self.max_depth or self.max_depth == 0:
            folder_list.insert(0, parent_item)

        folder_list.extend(file_list)

        return folder_list

        # Filter out parent items that would exceed max_depth
        # max_depth=0 means only parent navigation (no subdirectories)
        # max_depth>0 means unlimited navigation from initial folder
        parent_item = v.ListItem(
            value=str(self._initial_folder),
            children=[
                v.ListItemAction(
                    children=[
                        v.Icon(
                            color=self.ICON_STYLE["PARENT"]["color"][v.theme.dark],
                            children=[self.ICON_STYLE["PARENT"]["icon"]],
                        )
                    ]
                ),
                v.ListItemContent(
                    children=[v.ListItemTitle(children=[f".. /{self._initial_folder.name}"])]
                ),
            ],
        )

        # Always add the initial folder as parent (to navigate back to start)
        # unless current depth exceeds max_depth
        if current_depth <= self.max_depth:
            folder_list.insert(0, parent_item)

        folder_list.extend(file_list)

        return folder_list

"""Test the max_depth parameter for FileInput"""
import pytest
from pathlib import Path
import sepal_ui.sepalwidgets as sw


def test_max_depth_default():
    """Test that max_depth defaults to 0 (unlimited navigation)"""
    file_input = sw.FileInput()
    assert file_input.max_depth == 0


def test_max_depth_custom():
    """Test that max_depth can be set to a custom value"""
    file_input = sw.FileInput(max_depth=2)
    assert file_input.max_depth == 2


def test_max_depth_with_folder():
    """Test max_depth works with folder parameter"""
    root_dir = Path('/testbed')
    file_input = sw.FileInput(folder=root_dir, max_depth=1)
    assert file_input.max_depth == 1
    assert file_input._initial_folder == root_dir


def test_max_depth_parent_navigation():
    """Test that parent navigation works correctly with max_depth"""
    root_dir = Path('/testbed')
    file_input = sw.FileInput(folder=root_dir, max_depth=0)

    # With max_depth=0, only parent navigation should be available
    # The parent should always point to the initial folder
    parent_value = file_input._get_items()[0].value
    assert str(root_dir) in parent_value
    assert "testbed" in parent_value


def test_max_depth_initial_folder():
    """Test that _initial_folder is set correctly"""
    root_dir = Path('/home/user/projects')
    file_input = sw.FileInput(folder=root_dir)

    assert file_input._initial_folder == root_dir
    assert file_input.folder == root_dir


def test_max_depth_resets_to_initial():
    """Test that navigating back to initial folder is always possible"""
    root_dir = Path('/testbed')
    file_input = sw.FileInput(folder=root_dir)

    # Navigate to a subfolder
    subfolder = root_dir / "docs"
    file_input._on_file_select({"new": subfolder})

    # Parent should still point to initial folder
    items = file_input._get_items()
    parent_value = items[0].value
    assert str(root_dir) in parent_value
    assert parent_value.endswith("testbed")


def test_max_depth_depth_calculation():
    """Test that current depth is calculated correctly"""
    root_dir = Path('/testbed')
    file_input = sw.FileInput(folder=root_dir)

    # Initial depth should be 0
    assert file_input._get_items()  # Call to trigger depth calculation

    # Navigate to subfolder
    subfolder = root_dir / "docs"
    file_input._on_file_select({"new": subfolder})

    # Depth should be 1 (docs is 1 level deep from testbed)
    # This is tested implicitly by checking that parent is shown


if __name__ == "__main__":
    test_max_depth_default()
    test_max_depth_custom()
    test_max_depth_with_folder()
    test_max_depth_parent_navigation()
    test_max_depth_initial_folder()
    test_max_depth_resets_to_initial()
    test_max_depth_depth_calculation()
    print("All max_depth tests passed!")
